  "prompt": "What is the salary of vlsi fresher in India?",
  "response": "The salary for a VLSI (Very Large Scale Integration) fresher in India can vary based on several factors such as the company, location, and individual qualifications. On average, a VLSI fresher can expect a salary ranging from \u20b93.5 lakh to \u20b96 lakh per annum. \n\nHere's a more detailed breakdown:\n\n- **Tier-1 Cities (e.g., Bangalore, Hyderabad, Pune):** Salaries tend to be on the higher side, typically ranging from \u20b94.5 lakh to \u20b96 lakh per annum.\n- **Tier-2 Cities:** Salaries might be slightly lower, often ranging from \u20b93.5 lakh to \u20b95 lakh per annum.\n\nKeep in mind that these figures are approximate and can vary. Additionally, strong academic performance, relevant internships, and additional skills can influence the starting salary.",
